<h4>Host Registration URL</h4>
<hr>
<h5>What base URL should hosts use to connect to the {{settings.appName}} API?</h5>

<div class="r-mt15">
  <label style="width: 150px;">{{radio-button selection=customRadio value="no"}}&nbsp;This site's address:&nbsp;&nbsp;</label>
  <code class="form-control-static r-pl20 r-pr20">{{thisPage}}</code>
</div>

<div class="r-mt10">
  <label style="width: 150px;">{{radio-button selection=customRadio value="yes"}}&nbsp;Something else:&nbsp;&nbsp;</label>
  {{input type="text" class="form-control" value=customValue placeholder="e.g. http://example.com:8080" safeStyle="width: calc(100% - 170px); display: inline-block;  min-width: 300px;"}}
  <p class="help-block">
    Don't include <code>/v1</code> or any other path, but if you are doing
    {{#if settings.isRancher}}
      <a href="{{docsBase}}/installing-rancher/installing-server/basic-ssl-config/" target="_blank">SSL termination</a>
    {{else}}
      SSL termination
    {{/if}}
    in front of {{settings.appName}}, be sure to use <code>https://</code>.
  </p>
</div>

{{#unless looksPublic}}
  <div class="alert alert-info" style="margin-top: 30px;">
    <i class="icon icon-info" style="font-size: 35px; float: left;"></i>
    <p style="margin-left: 50px;">
      Are you sure all the hosts you will create will be able to reach <code>{{activeValue}}</code> ?<br/>It looks like a private IP or local network.
    </p>
  </div>
{{/unless}}

{{top-errors errors=errors}}

{{save-cancel cancelDisabled=true editing=true save="save"}}
